00:28.000 --> 00:29.000
No, no, no.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.000
I like the aisle seem better.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
Please, you sit by the window.

00:39.000 --> 00:40.000
My name is Stewart.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
Malcolm Stewart.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.000
Please, to meet you.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.000
I'm Elsa Tobin.

00:43.000 --> 00:44.000
How do you do?

00:44.000 --> 00:52.000
Do you live in New York?

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
No, no.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
I'm from Florida.

00:55.000 --> 00:57.000
I am too.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
But, didn't you just get on?

01:00.000 --> 01:03.000
No, I just changed my seat.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.000
A man next to me was smoking and smoke.

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
Really bothers me.

01:11.000 --> 01:13.000
Where are you from in Florida?

01:13.000 --> 01:14.000
That tightest feel.

01:14.000 --> 01:15.000
It's near Orlando.

01:15.000 --> 01:18.000
A small world, I'm from Titusville, too.

01:18.000 --> 01:19.000
Really?

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
What part?

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
My husband and I live near Spaceport.

01:25.000 --> 01:27.000
I know that area.

01:27.000 --> 01:31.000
My house is only a few miles from Spaceport.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Do you still live there?

01:33.000 --> 01:34.000
Oh, yes, yes.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
My husband's there now.

01:36.000 --> 01:40.000
He couldn't take time off to come to New York with me.

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
Do you still live there?

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
No.

01:46.000 --> 01:50.000
I sold the house and the furniture.

01:50.000 --> 01:57.000
Put a few personal things in an old trunk and shipped it to my children in New York.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
That's my destination.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
Are you married?

02:01.000 --> 02:04.000
My wife died four years ago.

02:04.000 --> 02:09.000
He was a wonderful woman, a real friend.

02:09.000 --> 02:10.000
I'm sorry.

02:10.000 --> 02:11.000
Really?

02:11.000 --> 02:14.000
I'm sorry.

02:14.000 --> 02:17.000
Lots of wonderful memories.

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
We were married almost 50 years.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
Well, 47 to be exact.

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
John and I celebrate our 40th anniversary next month.

02:25.000 --> 02:27.000
Oh, congratulations.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
That's nice.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
What does John do?

02:32.000 --> 02:37.000
He's an aerospace engineer and works for Orlando aircraft corporation.

02:37.000 --> 02:41.000
He started with them almost 40 years ago.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
What do you do?

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
I just retired.

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
Had my own company, a construction company.

02:49.000 --> 02:54.000
Wrong, redgers, big stuff.

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
But I just sold it and retired.

02:58.000 --> 03:02.000
Excuse me, ma'am.

03:02.000 --> 03:06.000
Take it, please.

03:06.000 --> 03:11.000
Would you kindly hold these keys, please?

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
I have a ticket.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
I know.

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
I was in the smoking section.

03:18.000 --> 03:19.000
It's okay, lady.

03:19.000 --> 03:21.000
Take your time.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.000
I'm sure it's in your apartment, Mrs. Tobin.

03:24.000 --> 03:29.000
Oh, here it is.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.000
And here are your keys.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
Thank you.

03:34.000 --> 03:41.000
Do you have family in New York?

03:41.000 --> 03:42.000
No, no.

03:42.000 --> 03:46.000
But I do have very close friends in New York City.

03:46.000 --> 03:49.000
We like to go to the theater together.

03:49.000 --> 03:51.000
You said you, me, in New York.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
Yes, indeed.

03:53.000 --> 03:57.000
A son and his wife and their three children.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.000
My grandchildren.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
You must be excited.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
I can't wait to see them.

04:03.000 --> 04:05.000
Are you going to live with them?

04:05.000 --> 04:06.000
Yes.

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
Permanent life?

04:08.000 --> 04:12.000
Well, they want me to.

04:12.000 --> 04:15.000
But it's too early to know for sure.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
I'm pretty independent.

04:17.000 --> 04:22.000
I tried to teach my kids the importance of independence.

04:22.000 --> 04:27.000
But I'm not sure I want to be alone.

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
Some people don't mind being alone.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.000
I do.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
I understand.

04:36.000 --> 04:41.000
But tell me, why did you stop working?

04:41.000 --> 04:46.000
I retired because of...

04:46.000 --> 04:49.000
I wanted to be with my family.

04:49.000 --> 04:52.000
I didn't want to be alone anymore.

